3 Data exclusions

Frequency of excluding, reporting, and reporting the exact number of participants (part), stimuli, and trials due to:

aux_df <- analysis_sample %>%
    select(pseudo_ResponseID,
         contains("_ExtEvent_"),
         contains("_FixedCr_"),
         contains("_DataDepCr_")) %>%
    select(-contains("feedback"),
         -contains("importance"))
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    pivot_longer(-pseudo_ResponseID,
             names_to = "var_name",
             values_to = "var_value")
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    mutate(var_name = str_sub(var_name, start = 6)) %>%
    mutate(var_name = str_replace(var_name, "excl", "Exclude")) %>%
    mutate(var_name = str_replace(var_name, "rep_exact", "ReportExact")) %>%
    mutate(var_name = str_replace(var_name, "rep", "Report"))
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    separate(var_name,
           into = c("excl_due_to", "do_what", "level_of_data"),
           sep = "_")
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    mutate(var_value = factor(var_value,
                      levels = c(NA,
                             "Never",
                             "Sometimes",
                             "About half the time",
                             "Most of the time",
                             "Always"),
                      labels = c("n.a.",
                             "Never",
                             "Sometimes",
                             "About half the time",
                             "Most of the time",
                             "Always"),
                      exclude = NULL))

df_exclude <- aux_df %>%
    filter(do_what == "Exclude")

df_report <- df_exclude %>%
    filter(var_value %in% c("Sometimes",
                    "About half the time",
                    "Most of the time",
                    "Always")) %>%
    select(pseudo_ResponseID,
         excl_due_to,
         level_of_data) %>%
    left_join(aux_df %>%
                filter(do_what %in% c("Report", "ReportExact")),
            by = c("pseudo_ResponseID", "excl_due_to", "level_of_data"))

aux_df <- rbind(df_exclude,
            df_report)

aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    mutate(level_of_data = factor(level_of_data,
                        levels = c("part",
                                 "stimuli",
                                 "trials"),
                        labels = c("Participants",
                                 "Stimuli",
                                 "Trials"))) %>%
    mutate(do_what = factor(do_what,
                    levels = c("Exclude",
                             "Report",
                             "ReportExact"),
                    labels = c("Exclude",
                             "Report excluding",
                             "Report the exact number\nof excluded observations")))

aux_df %>%

Checks against reports for how often observations are excluded.

Participants report how often they exclude observations for each of three exclusion criteria and three types of observations (i.e., participants, stimuli, trials). This corresponds to each participant providing nine responses to How often do you exclude ?. Participants who exclude observations at least sometimes for each of the nine combinations (exclusion criteria * type of observations) have a score of 9.

aux_df <- df_frequency %>%
    filter(do_what == "Exclude")
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    mutate(is_excluding = if_else(var_value %in% c("Sometimes",
                                     "About half the time",
                                     "Most of the time",
                                     "Always"), 
                        1, 0))
aux_df <- aux_df %>%
    group_by(pseudo_ResponseID) %>%
    summarise(n_times_excluding = sum(is_excluding)) %>%
    ungroup()

aux_df %>%
    group_by(n_times_excluding) %>%
    summarise(n()) %>%
    ungroup()
## # A tibble: 9  2

All participants exclude observations for at least one of the nine situations. Eight participants report excluding observations for all of the nine criteria and types combinations. Next, I will calculate an average score of how often each participants reports the exact number of excluded observations (average over the nine situations).

aux_test <- df_frequency %>%
    filter(do_what == "Report the exact number\nof excluded observations")
aux_test <- aux_test %>%
    mutate(num_value = as.integer(var_value) - 2)
aux_test %>%
    group_by(num_value,
           var_value) %>%
    summarise(n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'num_value'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
## # A tibble: 6  3
## # Groups:   num_value [6]
##   num_value var_value           `n()`
##       <dbl> <fct>               <int>
## 1        -1 n.a.                    2
## 2         0 Never                  17
## 3         1 Sometimes              24
## 4         2 About half the time     7
## 5         3 Most of the time       36
## 6         4 Always                254
aux_test <- aux_test %>%
    mutate(num_value = if_else(num_value == -1, 0, num_value))
aux_test <- aux_test %>%
    group_by(pseudo_ResponseID) %>%
    summarise(num_value = mean(num_value)) %>%
    ungroup()
aux_test <- aux_test %>%
    left_join(analysis_sample %>%
                select(pseudo_ResponseID,
                     likelihood_reproduce),
            by = c("pseudo_ResponseID"))
